Package uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.machine.tags

Class IPTag

java.lang.Object
uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.machine.tags.Tag
uk.ac.manchester.spinnaker.machine.tags.IPTag
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Comparable<Tag>
public final class IPTag
extends Tag
Used to hold data that is contained within an IP tag. IP tags allow data to flow at runtime from SpiNNaker to the outside world.

    • IPTag

      public IPTag​(java.lang.String boardAddress, int tagID, int x, int y, java.lang.String targetAddress, java.lang.Integer port, java.lang.Boolean stripSDP, java.lang.String trafficIdentifier) throws java.net.UnknownHostException
      Constructor for JSON deserialization.
      Parameters:
      boardAddress - The IP address of the board on which the tag is allocated
      tagID - The ID of the tag (0..7)
      x - The X coordinate of the destination.
      y - The Y coordinate of the destination.
      targetAddress - The IP address to which SDP packets with the tag will be sent
      port - The port to which the SDP packets with the tag will be sent, or null if not yet assigned.
      stripSDP - Indicates whether the SDP header should be removed
      trafficIdentifier - The identifier for traffic transmitted using this tag
      Throws:
      java.net.UnknownHostException - If an IP address doesn't resolve.
